Hello! My team is trying to set up photonvision for position data in a Java CommandRobot. Adding a PhotonCamera has seemed to work fine:

PhotonCamera camera = new PhotonCamera(“pvcam”);

(the camera is named pvcam in the web interface)

But adding a GetLatestResult() to the periodic or a button causes a lot of errors. The issue seems to be the startCompetition() method. The code builds, but after it is deployed and before it is enabled, the error causes the roboRIO to lose robot code (I think. DriverStation says there is no robot code). Here are the errors that come up in red in VSCode:
Unhandled exception: java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: Index 10 out of bounds for length 10
Error at org.photonvision.common.dataflow.structures.Packet.decodeShort(Packet.java:214): Unhandled exception: java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: Index 10 out of bounds for length 10

…

The startCompetition() method (or methods called by it) should have handled the exception above.

And here’s the full stack trace:
Unhandled exception: java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: Index 10 out of bounds for length 10

Error at org.photonvision.common.dataflow.structures.Packet.decodeShort(Packet.java:214): Unhandled exception: java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: Index 10 out of bounds for length 10

Looks like you have a mismatch between your PhotonVision and Photonlib versions. Keep in mind the online url used in VSCode to install the photonlib json uses the latest version, which means it currently pulls version v2024.1.1-beta-3.2. If you want to use an older photonlib version, you can change the instances of "version" in the json file to the desired release-- for the last 2023 version, this is "v2023.4.2".
